April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n| website         = [https://www.santepubliquefrance.fr/maladies-et-traumatismes/maladies-et-infections-respiratoires/infection-a-coronavirus/articles/infection-au-nouveau-coronavirus-sars-cov-2-covid-19-france-et-monde Public Health France]\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|<noinclude>2019\u201320 coronavirus </noinclude>pandemic]] reached [[France]] on 24 January 2020, when the first [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] case in Europe and France was confirmed in [[Bordeaux]]. The first five confirmed cases were all individuals who had recently arrived or returned from China.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite news|last1=Jacob|first1=Etienne|url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences/coronavirus-trois-premiers-cas-confirmes-en-france-20200124|title=Coronavirus: trois premiers cas confirm\u00e9s en France|date=24 January 2020|work=Le Figaro|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Bernard-Stoecklin|first=S|date=13 February 2020|title=First cases of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) in France: surveillance, investigations and control measures, January 2020|journal=Eurosurveillance|volume=25|issue=6|pages=2000094|doi=10.2807/1560-7917.ES.2020.25.6.2000094|pmid=32070465|pmc=7029452}}</ref> On 28 January, a Chinese tourist carrying the virus was admitted to hospital in Paris and died on 14 February, making it the first death in France.<ref name=\"StraitsTimesFourthCase\">{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/france-confirms-fourth-case-of-coronavirus-in-elderly-chinese-tourist|title=Wuhan virus: France confirms fourth case of coronavirus in elderly Chinese tourist|date=29 January 2020|website=The Straits Times|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200220191811/https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/france-confirms-fourth-case-of-coronavirus-in-elderly-chinese-tourist|archive-date=20 February 2020|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC-first-case-europe\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51514837|title=First coronavirus death confirmed in Europe|date=15 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219204410/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51514837|archive-date=19 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/29/national/japan-support-for-coronavirus-hit-wuhan/|title=Support efforts begin across Japan to help coronavirus-hit Wuhan|work=[[Japan Times]]|access-date=30 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://apnews.com/e96365aa6ba46ba6bef50a0673301985|title=France announces 1st death of virus patient outside Asia|last=Ganley|first=Elaine|date=15 February 2020|agency=[[Associated Press]]|url-status=live|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOne key event in the spread of the disease across Metropolitan France as well as its overseas territories was the annual assembly of the [[Christian Open Door Church]] between 17 and 24 February in [[Mulhouse]] which was attended by about 2,500 people, at least half of whom are believed to have contracted the virus.<ref name=\"lepoint2369173\">{{cite web|url=https://www.lepoint.fr/sante/coronavirus-la-bombe-atomique-du-rassemblement-evangelique-de-mulhouse-28-03-2020-2369173_40.php|title=Coronavirus : la \" bombe atomique \" du rassemblement \u00e9vang\u00e9lique de Mulhouse|date=28 March 2020|website=Le Point}}</ref><ref name=\"francetvinfo3889133\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/video-coronavirus-le-nombre-de-contaminations-lors-du-rassemblement-evangelique-de-mulhouse-a-ete-largement-sous-evalue_3889133.html|title=ENQUETE FRANCEINFO. \"La majorit\u00e9 des personnes \u00e9taient contamin\u00e9es\" : de la Corse \u00e0 l'outre-mer, comment le rassemblement \u00e9vang\u00e9lique de Mulhouse a diffus\u00e9 le coronavirus dans toute la France|date=28 March 2020|website=Franceinfo}}</ref>\n\n<onlyinclude>{{#ifeq:{{{transcludesection|FrenchDomesticResponse}}}|FrenchDomesticResponse|\nOn 12 March, French President [[Emmanuel Macron]] announced on public television that all schools and all universities would close from Monday 16 March until further notice. The next day, the prime minister [[\u00c9douard Philippe]] banned gatherings of more than 100 people, not including public transport. The following day, the prime minister ordered the closure of all non-essential public places, including restaurants, caf\u00e9s, cinemas and nightclubs, effective at midnight.<ref name=\"bbc51892477\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51892477|title=Coronavirus: Spain and France announce sweeping restrictions|work=BBC News|date=15 March 2020|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref> On 16 March, President Macron announced mandatory home confinement for 15 days starting at noon on 17 March.<ref name=\"independent9405136\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-france-lockdown-cases-update-covid-19-macron-a9405136.html|title=France imposes 15-day lockdown as part of emergency coronavirus response|date=16 March 2020|website=The Independent}}</ref>}}</onlyinclude> On 27 March, Prime Minister \u00c9douard Philippe extended the lockdown until 15 April.<ref name=\"independent9405136\"/> On 8 April 2020, President Macron announced the lockdown would be extended once more.<ref>[https://www.france24.com/en/20200408-france-to-extend-coronavirus-lockdown-again-will-run-beyond-april-15 France to extend coronavirus lockdown again, will run beyond April 15] 8 April 2020 ''www.france24.com'', accessed 9 April 2020</ref> On 13 April, he announced that the lockdown period would be extended until 11 May<ref name=\"macron13april\">{{cite news|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/direct-coronavirus-prolongation-du-confinement-reouverture-des-ecoles-et-des-commerces-regardez-l-allocution-televisee-d-emmanuel-macron_3913673.html|title=Coronavirus : prolongation du confinement jusqu'au 11 mai|date=2020-04-13|publisher=[[France Info (TV channel)|France Info]]|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>, after which a progressive lifting of confinement would occur as face masks would be made available to all citizens.\n\n{{As of|2020|4|17|alt=As of 17 April}}, France has reported over 168 000 confirmed cases, 18,680 deaths, and 34,400 recoveries,<ref name=\"dashboard Covid19 France\">{{cite web|url=https://dashboard.covid19.data.gouv.fr/|title=COVID-19 en France|publisher=Sant\u00e9 Publique France|language=fr|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> making it the forth highest country by number of confirmed cases, now overtaking China where the outbreak first began.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/world/coronavirus-maps.html Coronavirus Map: Tracking the Global Outbreak] ''The New York Times''. Retrieved 4 April 2020</ref> France also counts nursing home deaths since 2 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200403-french-hospitals-record-deadliest-day-with-588-coronavirus-deaths|title=French hospitals record deadliest day with 588 coronavirus deaths|date=3 April 2020|publisher=France 24|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref> {{As of|2020|4|8|alt=As of 8 April}} France has reported 30,902 confirmed or suspected cases in retirement homes. (These figures are now included in the national tally.)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.santepubliquefrance.fr/maladies-et-traumatismes/maladies-et-infections-respiratoires/infection-a-coronavirus/articles/infection-au-nouveau-coronavirus-sars-cov-2-covid-19-france-et-monde|title=Infection au nouveau Coronavirus (SARS-CoV-2), COVID-19, France et Monde|website=Sant\u00e9 publique France|language=French|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.liberation.fr/france/2020/04/02/au-moins-884-morts-dans-les-maisons-de-retraite-et-ehpad_1784033|title=Covid-19: au moins 884 morts dans les maisons de retraite et Ehpad |website=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|language=French|date=2020-04-02|access-date=2020-04-11|quote=''L\u2019opacit\u00e9 se l\u00e8ve. Alors que de plus en plus de voix s\u2019\u00e9levaient depuis une dizaine de jours pour que la lumi\u00e8re soit faite sur les m\u00e9faits du Covid-19 sur les personnes \u00e2g\u00e9es plac\u00e9es dans des \u00e9tablissements ad hoc (plus de 7 500 sur tout le territoire), les premiers chiffres ont \u00e9t\u00e9 r\u00e9v\u00e9l\u00e9s ce jeudi soir par le directeur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la Sant\u00e9, J\u00e9r\u00f4me Salomon''}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nThe pandemic occurred in the backdrop of a protracted [[2019\u201320 French pension reform strike|national protests]] against pension reforms proposed by President [[Emmanuel Macron]] as part of his election manifesto.<ref>{{cite news |title=Macron pension reform: Strike continues for second day |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-50682071 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=6 December 2019|date=6 December 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Amaro |first1=Silvia |title=France's worst strike in decades enters a second day |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/12/06/france-strikes-for-a-second-day-over-macron-pension-reform-plans.html |publisher=CNBC |accessdate=6 December 2019}}</ref> This is the longest strike in modern French history.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-50971439|title=French transport strike now longest in 50 years|date=2020-01-02|access-date=2020-01-12|language=en-GB}}</ref> In President Emmanuel Macron's second address to the nation on the pandemic on 16 March, he announced the suspension of all reforms, notably that of pensions.<ref>[https://www.huffingtonpost.fr/entry/coronavirus-la-reforme-des-retraites-suspendue-annonce-macron_fr_5e6fd329c5b60fb69ddc13c9 Coronavirus: la r\u00e9forme des retraites suspendue annonce Macron] 16 March 2020 ''www.huffingtonpost.fr'', accessed 12 April 2020</ref>\n\nOn 12 January, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, who had initially come to the attention of the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=\"Elsevier\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center|last=Elsevier|date=|website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Matt|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic?|date=4 March 2020|work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|issn=1357-0978}}</ref> On 21 January, [[Agn\u00e8s Buzyn]], [[Minister of Health (France)|Minister of Solidarity and Health]] declared that \"The risk of introduction into France is low but it cannot be excluded\". <ref name=\"BuzynJanuary21\">{{cite news|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/societe/sante/coronavirus-le-risque-d-introduction-en-france-est-faible-mais-il-ne-peut-etre-exclu-selon-agnes-buzyn-21-01-2020-8241345.php|title=Coronavirus : \"Le risque d'introduction en France est faible mais il ne peut \u00eatre exclu\", selon Agn\u00e8s Buzyn|date=2020-01-21|publisher=[[Le Parisien]]|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/France medical cases chart}}\n===First confirmed cases===\nOn 23 January, the French [[Minister of Health (France)|Minister of Health]] office also officially published the same analysis on the situation.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://solidarites-sante.gouv.fr/soins-et-maladies/maladies/maladies-infectieuses/coronavirus/etat-des-lieux-et-actualites/article/points-de-situation-coronavirus-covid-19#Point%20du%2023%20janvier%202020|title=Point du 23 janvier 2020|date=23 January 2020|publisher=[[Minister of Health (France)|French Minister of Health]]|access-date=12 April 2020|quote=''Le risque d'introduction est faible mais ne peut pas \u00eatre exclu.''}}</ref> The same day [[Air France]] suspended its flights from and to [[Wuhan]], and reduced the frequency of its flights from and to Beijing and Shanghai.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.europe1.fr/international/coronavirus-air-france-suspend-ses-vols-vers-wuhan-et-reduit-ceux-vers-pekin-et-shanghai-3946372|title=Coronavirus : Air France suspend ses vols vers Wuhan et r\u00e9duit ceux vers P\u00e9kin et Shanghai|date=29 January 2020|publisher=[[Europe 1]]|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 January, the first COVID-19 case in Europe was confirmed in [[Bordeaux]]. A 48-year-old French citizen from China, who arrived in France on 22 January, was hospitalised at Centre Hospitalier Universitaire de Bordeaux. [[Service d'Aide M\u00e9dicale Urgente]] took charge and the patient was isolated in the hospital. The authorities tried to confirm whether he had infected people who were in contact with him.<ref name=\"francetvinfo3799837\">{{cite news|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/coronavirus-en-france-le-parcours-des-trois-patients_3799837.html|title=Coronavirus en France : le parcours des trois patients|date=24 January 2020|work=France Info|access-date=26 February 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221231826/https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/coronavirus-en-france-le-parcours-des-trois-patients_3799837.html|archive-date=21 February 2020|language=fr}}</ref>. Agn\u00e8s Buzyn then said that \"The risks of propagation of the virus in France are extremely low\".<ref name=\"BuzynJanuary24\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bfmtv.com/mediaplayer/video/coronavirus-en-france-les-risques-de-propagation-du-virus-dans-la-population-sont-tres-faibles-selon-agnes-buzyn-1217484.html|title=Coronavirus : en France, \"les risques de propagation du virus dans la population sont tr\u00e8s faibles\" selon Agn\u00e8s Buzyn|date=24 January 2020|publisher=[[BFM TV]]|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> Two more cases were confirmed in Paris by the end of the day \u2013 a couple who had returned from China on 18 January.<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":11\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-outbreak-hospital-to-be-built-in-five-days-as-death-toll-rises-in-china-11916211|title=Coronavirus outbreak: First confirmed cases in Europe as France declares two infections|publisher=Sky News|access-date=24 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"lemonde6027158\">{{cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/01/24/coronavirus-deux-premiers-cas-confirmes-en-france-a-bordeaux-et-paris_6027158_3244.html|title=Coronavirus : deux premi\u00e8res contaminations confirm\u00e9es en France|date=24 January 2020|work=Le Monde|access-date=24 January 2020|language=fr}}</ref> The 31-year-old man and his 30-year-old partner, both from [[Wuhan]], tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 and were hospitalised at [[Bichat\u2013Claude Bernard Hospital]] in Paris. On 26 January, Buzyn declared that the French government had millions of masks which could be distributed to the population if necessary.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.liberation.fr/checknews/2020/02/27/covid-19-y-a-t-il-une-penurie-de-masques-de-protection_1779861|title=Covid-19 : y a-t-il une p\u00e9nurie de masques de protection pour les professionnels de sant\u00e9? |date=27 January 2020|work=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bfmtv.com/mediaplayer/video/coronavirus-agnes-buzyn-estime-totalement-inutile-le-port-de-masque-pour-les-non-contamines-1217820.html|title=Coronavirus: Agn\u00e8s Buzyn estime \"totalement inutile\" le port de masque pour les non-contamin\u00e9s |date=26 January 2020|publisher=[[BFM TV]]|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 January, an 80-year-old Chinese tourist from Hubei tested positive and was hospitalised at Bichat\u2013Claude Bernard Hospital,<ref name=\"StraitsTimesFourthCase\" /> the following day, his 50-year-old daughter tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital.<ref name=\"lexpress2116745\">{{cite web |title=Cinqui\u00e8me case aver\u00e9 |url=https://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/sante/coronavirus-un-cinquieme-cas-avere-en-france-la-fille-du-quatrieme-malade_2116745.html |website=L'Express |accessdate=29 January 2020 |date=29 January 2020 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129193013/https://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/sante/coronavirus-un-cinquieme-cas-avere-en-france-la-fille-du-quatrieme-malade_2116745.html |archive-date=29 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The death of the 80-year-old on 14 February marked the first death from COVID-19 outside of Asia.<ref name=\"BBC-first-case-europe\" />\n\nOn 30 January, a Paris doctor who had come into contact with a Chinese tourist whose infection was confirmed upon her return to China was confirmed positive for COVID-19.<ref name=\"leparisien8248956\">{{cite web|title=Coronavirus: un sixi\u00e8me cas confirm\u00e9|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/societe/coronavirus-un-sixieme-cas-confirme-en-france-un-medecin-confine-a-paris-30-01-2020-8248956.php|website=[[Le Parisien]]|accessdate=30 January 2020|date=30 January 2020|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131112945/http://www.leparisien.fr/societe/coronavirus-un-sixieme-cas-confirme-en-france-un-medecin-confine-a-paris-30-01-2020-8248956.php|archive-date=31 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March 2020, the [[Direction g\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la Sant\u00e9]] (DGS) asked ''Sant\u00e9 publique France'' to buy ''urgently'' 1,1&nbsp;million of [[FFP mask#FFP2 mask|FFP2 mask]]s.<ref>{{cite web|title=Masques: les preuves d'un mensonge d'Etat |url=https://www.mediapart.fr/journal/france/020420/masques-les-preuves-d-un-mensonge-d-etat|website=[[Mediapart]]|date=17 March 2020|accessdate=13 April 2020|language=fr|quote=''Le 24 janvier, la Direction g\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la sant\u00e9 (DGS) saisit l\u2019agence Sant\u00e9 publique France (SPF), sous la tutelle du minist\u00e8re, pour faire un inventaire des stocks de mat\u00e9riel m\u00e9dical. Le 30 janvier, elle lui demande d'acqu\u00e9rir \u00ab d\u00e8s que possible \u00bb 1,1 million de masques FFP2 seulement, selon un document obtenu par Mediapart''}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January, Marie Fontanel, the President counselor for solidarity and health, quit her job to help her husband in the coming municipal elections. She would be replaced only one month later.<ref>{{cite web|title=L'\u00e9tonnant d\u00e9part de la conseill\u00e8re sant\u00e9 d'Emmanuel Macron  |url=https://www.mediapart.fr/journal/france/050420/l-etonnant-depart-de-la-conseillere-sante-d-emmanuel-macron|website=[[Mediapart]]|date=17 March 2020|accessdate=13 April 2020|language=fr|quote=''Conseill\u00e8re sant\u00e9 du pr\u00e9sident de la R\u00e9publique depuis le d\u00e9but du quinquennat, Marie Fontanel a quitt\u00e9 l\u2019\u00c9lys\u00e9e le 31 janvier, alors que l\u2019OMS venait de d\u00e9clarer \u00ab l\u2019urgence de sant\u00e9 publique de port\u00e9e internationale \u00bb. Elle n\u2019a \u00e9t\u00e9 remplac\u00e9e qu\u2019un mois plus tard. Cette vacance interroge de nouveau sur la gestion de la crise sanitaire par le pouvoir, au moment o\u00f9 la menace pand\u00e9mique se profilait d\u00e9j\u00e0.''}}</ref> The same day, all the countries of the [[Schengen Area]], except France, suspend [[Travel visa|visas]] with China.<ref>{{cite web|title=Confirmed: All Schengen Countries, but France, Have Suspended Visa Issuance in China|url=https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/confirmed-all-schengen-countries-but-france-have-suspended-visa-issuance-in-china/|website=[[Mediapart]]|accessdate=13 April 2020|date=1 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible\" style=\"margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;\"\n|-\n!Case\n!Date\n!Age\n!Gender\n!Nationality\n!Hospital admitted to\n!Source of infection\n!Status\n!Note\n!Source\n|-\n|1\n| rowspan=\"3\" |24 January 2020\n|48\n|Male\n|French\n|H\u00f4pital Pellegrin, [[Bordeaux]]\n|rowspan=\"5\" |China\n|Discharged\n|First case in Europe. Wine merchant back from China. Out of hospital on 13 February.\n|<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.20minutes.fr/bordeaux/2703783-20200126-coronavirus-sait-cas-detecte-bordeaux|title=Coronavirus : Que sait-on du cas d\u00e9tect\u00e9 \u00e0 Bordeaux ?|last=Provenzano|first=Elsa|date=26 January 2020|work=20 Minutes|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219143036/https://www.20minutes.fr/bordeaux/2703783-20200126-coronavirus-sait-cas-detecte-bordeaux|archive-date=19 February 2020|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/epidemie-de-coronavirus-le-premier-malade-diagnostique-en-france-affirme-etre-sorti-de-l-hopital_3824827.html|title=Epid\u00e9mie de coronavirus : le premier malade diagnostiqu\u00e9 en France affirme \u00eatre gu\u00e9ri et sorti de l'h\u00f4pital|date=13 February 2020|website=Franceinfo|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215004230/https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/epidemie-de-coronavirus-le-premier-malade-diagnostique-en-france-affirme-etre-sorti-de-l-hopital_3824827.html|archive-date=15 February 2020|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|2\n|30\n|Male\n| rowspan=\"4\" |Chinese\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[H\u00f4pital Bichat]], Paris\n|Discharged\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Couple living in France back from China. Out of hospital on 12 February.\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref name=\"lefigaro20200124\">{{cite web|url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences/coronavirus-trois-premiers-cas-confirmes-en-france-20200124|ti